WEBVTT

00:00:00.151 --> 00:00:05.892
Leading geographically dispersed virtual teams introduces friction known as social distance.

00:00:06.573 --> 00:00:10.634
The split framework identifies five components that create this distance.

00:00:11.374 --> 00:00:13.834
Consider a worked example of a virtual team.

00:00:14.554 --> 00:00:19.336
First, the structure of reporting lines becomes obscured without physical proximity.

00:00:19.816 --> 00:00:24.877
This leads to a breakdown in process where workflows lose clarity and cause delays.

00:00:25.497 --> 00:00:29.223
Next, language differences hinder mutual understanding.

00:00:29.824 --> 00:00:32.429
This weakens the shared identity and purpose.

00:00:33.270 --> 00:00:37.717
Finally, reliance on technology amplifies feelings of disconnection.

00:00:38.479 --> 00:00:44.969
The mandate is to mitigate this distance by maintaining frequent, brief contact to validate contributions.
